1169
01:50:04,560 --> 01:50:10,480
There are a lot of podcasters in the world who 
will interview way more experts than I have,  

1170
01:50:10,480 --> 01:50:15,680
and I don't think they're much the 
wiser or more knowledgeable as a result. 

1171
01:50:15,680 --> 01:50:21,680
So it's clearly possible to mess this up.
I wonder if you have thoughts or takes or  

1172
01:50:21,680 --> 01:50:28,480
advice on how one actually learns in 
a deeper way from this kind of work. 

1173
01:50:29,120 --> 01:50:36,320
It's an incredibly complicated and rich question.
It seems like the question is,  

1174
01:50:37,280 --> 01:50:41,360
how do you make it a higher-growth context?
How do you make it a more demanding context? 

1175
01:50:42,560 --> 01:50:47,120
You can do that in relatively small ways 
that might yield compounding returns,  

1176
01:50:47,120 --> 01:50:52,880
