That used to just be annoying. 

1240
01:56:39,600 --> 01:56:46,480
Now it seems like it's maybe even the 
most important part of the whole process. 

1241
01:56:47,760 --> 01:56:53,280
That hard-won nature of it means 
that I internalize it afterwards. 

1242
01:56:53,280 --> 01:57:01,680
I've written 10,000-word essays in 
a couple of days, and I've written  

1243
01:57:01,680 --> 01:57:08,160
them in three months or six months.
I feel like I didn't learn very much  

1244
01:57:08,160 --> 01:57:15,520
from the ones that only took a couple of days.
